This paper deals with the optimization of a multiuser MIMO communication system, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) concepts. The paper also considers linear processing schemes, which fall under the category of signal processing (cs.SY). The optimization of training duration and power allocation involves mathematical modeling and optimization, which can be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
